	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64247014"><p>Of 23 US cities with populations of 750k or more, <a href="https://www.sfchronicle.com/crime/article/violent-crime-san-francisco-17880303.php" title="sfchronicle.com">San Francisco is #14/23 in violent crime<span class="substr"> </span></a> [sfchronicle.com].  On the subject of murders, it's even lower - #18/23 - one of the lowest among major US cities.  The only thing it ranks relatively highly on is property crime, which ironically is NOT what the US right complains about when talking about SF.  SF crime hit historic LOWS in 2020/2021, and in 2022 only inched back to pre-pandemic levels; it's overall been on a long-term downtrend (like most of the US).</p><p>It's a politically</p></div>
	</div>

